Levram

Target IP: 192.168.170.24

Scanning


There are only two ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 8000: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application.

I tried the default credentials admin:admin and I gained access to the web application.The application running on this port is Gerapy v0.9.7.


Doing a Google search shows this application is vulnerable to RCE.


I did a simple directory search using the command gobuster dir -u http://192.168.170.24:8000/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt and found a directory called /admin, as shown above.


And again using the default credentials admin:admin, I gained access to the Django application.

Exploitation



According to the exploit, there needs to be at least one project. Since I have access to the web application, I created a project called test.


I downloaded the exploit and ran it against the target machine. I got a shell!

Privilege Escalation


The binary /usr/bin/python3.10 has ep privileges.


Using this capability weakness, I spawned a root shell.

Flags


The local.txt flag once I gained a foothold on the machine as the user app.


The proof.txt flag once I used the Python binary with capability weakness to spawn a root shell.
